; Same llvm-ir parse-failure path, but with an operand so the generated module text
; carries a typed parameter (`i64 %0`) and the body exercises `$t0`/`$0` placeholder
; substitution before the (still invalid) opcode. Verifies the self-host reproduces
; the parameter list and substituted body verbatim in the `--- generated module ---`
; section, not just the zero-arg case.
(defn m [(x i64)] (-> i64) (llvm-ir i64 [x] "%r = bogusop $t0 $0, 1
ret $ret %r"))
